        <Title>PlatformKit</Title>
        <PackageReleaseNotes>## Changes since 2.4 series

### Additions
* Additions for Windows platform
     * Re-added new `GetWMIValue()` method
     * Added new Windows enums `WindowsEdition`
     * Added Windows Edition Detection
     * Move Windows analysis code to `WindowsAnalyzer` class - Existing methods in the WindowsSoftwareDetection class is deprecated and will be removed in PlatformKit 3.0
* Additions for macOS platform
     * Added in code documentation for `MacProcessorType` enum
     * macOS Detection support for:
          * XNU version
          * Darwin version
          * macOS version
          * macOS Build String
     * Re-added `RunMacCommand()` method
     * Re-added `MacSystemProfilerDataType` enum
     * Fixed macOS Runtime ID Generation now that macOS version detection exists in PlatformKit.
* Additions for all platforms
     * Added Shared Model `ReleaseYearModel` and Shared Enum `ReleaseYearTimeframe`
     * Changed `LinuxOsRelease` struct to a class
     * Added additional in code documentation

### Changes
* Clarified deprecation of `RunCommand` to suggest alternatives.
* Moved `ShowLicenseInConsole` method to `ConsoleHelper` class - A copy will remain in the PlatformManager class until PlatformKit V3
* Restructured folder and namespace directory
* Moved Windows Software Detection to separate files
* Changed several structs to Classes
* Fixed issues with Runtime ID Generation on Linux
* Fixed issues with detecting OsRelease information on Linux
* Minor Tweaks

### Deprecations
* macOS 10.13 support has been deprecated and will throw an error in V5.
* Delayed deprecation of Windows 8.1 and Windows Server 2012 R2 support from V4 to V5.
* Deprecated `RunActionOn` method - This will be removed in V3 and will not be replaced.
* Deprecated `IWinManagementObjectSearcher` interface - This will be removed in PlatformKit 3.0
* Deprecated `WindowsSoftwareDetection` class and `IWindowsSoftwareDetection` interface - This will be removed in PlatformKit 3.0

### Known Issues
* WinManagementObjectSearcher method `public Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt; Get(List&lt;string&gt; queryObjectsList, string wmiClass)` does not return WMI values correctly.
* `GetWMIValue()` method does not return WMI value correctly.</PackageReleaseNotes>
